        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(tools/write): add append mode for agent writes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRevives and rebases the closed append-mode work from #75549 for the canonical data-loss issue #40001.\n\nThe `write` tool currently overwrites existing files. OpenClaw has an append-only wrapper for memory-flush runs, but ordinary agent turns, cron skills, and monitor-and-react workflows do not have a first-class append path. This PR adds a backwards-compatible optional `append: true` parameter to `write` so agents can append without synthesizing a read-concatenate-overwrite sequence.\n\nWhen `append` is omitted or false, existing overwrite behavior is unchanged.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds optional `append?: boolean` handling for host/workspace and sandbox write operations.\n- Preserves existing workspace/root guard behavior.\n- Serializes concurrent appends through the existing file mutation queue.\n- Preserves validation behavior for blank paths and invalid content.\n- Surfaces sandbox I/O failures except for missing-file cases used to create-on-append.\n- Honors aborted append calls before entering the mutation queue.\n- Adds focused regression coverage for append-create, append-accumulate, append-false-overwrites, validation, and sandbox/workspace behavior.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun in an isolated checkout on current `origin/main`:\n\n- `corepack pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `corepack pnpm exec vitest run src/agents/pi-tools.workspace-only-false.test.ts src/agents/pi-tools.create-openclaw-coding-tools.test.ts src/agents/pi-tools.read.host-tilde-expansion.test.ts src/agents/pi-tools.sandbox-mounted-paths.workspace-only.test.ts src/agents/pi-tools.params.test.ts`\n  - passed: `10 files / 170 tests`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `corepack pnpm lint:core`\n  - passed: `0 warnings / 0 errors`\n\n## Notes\n\nThis PR intentionally keeps the API small and backwards-compatible. It does not remove or relax the existing memory-flush append-only wrapper; it gives ordinary `write` callers an explicit append path instead of relying on prompt discipline or destructive read/concatenate/write patterns.\n\nFixes #40001.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** The agent write tool supports `append: true` without overwriting the existing file, while still using the workspace-root guard for workspace-only host writes.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux using the actual `createHostWorkspaceWriteTool` implementation against a temporary workspace on the real filesystem.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran a `node --import tsx` terminal smoke that created the host workspace write tool, wrote `first line`, reran the same write tool with `append: true` for `second line`, then read the resulting file.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal capture from the smoke:\n\n  ```text\n  workspace: $TMPDIR/openclaw-write-append-proof-.../workspace\n  tool result: append:true preserved existing content and added the second line\n  file content:\n  first line\n  second line\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The final file retained the original content and appended the new content in order; the append path did not truncate or replace the file.\n- **What was not tested:** No live Gateway session was exercised; validation used the real tool implementation in an isolated local checkout plus targeted regression/type checks.\n",
        "branch": "feat/write-append-mode-revival",
